""""
Coding Exam Question 13

        Ask the user to enter a 3 digit number till he enters 0
        Print the square root of only 3 digit positive numbers.

        Make sure that the program does not print the square root of any number
        that is not a 3 digit number


"""

x = 1
while x != 0:
    x = int(input("enter a 3 digit number till he enters 0 : "))
    if x >= 100 and x < 1000:
        m = int(x)**0.5
        print("your 3 digit number square root is : ",int(m))
    elif x < 0:
        print("no negative or flot value please")
else:
    print("it is not a 3 digit number")
